      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/philosophy/domains/western/domains/marxism/texts/tutorial-tracing-dialectical-development/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a &lt;strong&gt;tutorial&lt;/strong&gt; text. It teaches one beginner workflow through a&#xA;small, guided exercise.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../terms/dialectics.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Dialectics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../terms/determinate-negation.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Determinate Negation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../terms/mediation.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Mediation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../terms/historicization.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Historicization&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;learning-objective&#34;&gt;Learning objective&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;By the end, you should be able to produce a five-line dialectical map of&#xA;a short argument.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-1-start-with-a-tiny-claim&#34;&gt;Step 1: Start with a tiny claim&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Use this toy claim:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;A labor market that treats labor as a commodity depends on stable&#xA;workers, yet competitive pressure destabilizes those workers&amp;rsquo; lives.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
